cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper deals with image analysis and machine learning techniques for counting the number of records in historical handwritten documents. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the results (cs.LG) and the potential applications of the proposed method in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
